[background arg="res://Bg/door.png" fade="3.0"]
set {chapter1_score} = 0
set {c1s2_repair_tried} = false
set {c1s2_teacher_tried} = false
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s2/The_time_is_now_530.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The time is now 5\:30. Today's classes are over. Instead of going home, the protagonist  and Mark stay in the classroom to talk.
	join Celestine (half) left
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Celestine: Finally, classes are over. Let's go find that Janitor!
	Mark: I can't, mom told me to go home as soon as possible. My mom and I got invited to celebrate my cousin's birthday. You know how my mom is.
	Celestine: Alright, fine. We can just talk through messages just in case I need you for something. You better respond as soon as you can.
	leave Mark [animation="Instant Out"]
	leave Celestine [animation="Instant Out"]
	[background arg="res://Bg/storage room front door.png" fade="0.0"]
	...
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s2/The_protagonist_immediately.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist  immediately went to the classroom.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s2/The_protagonist_chest.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	The protagonist's chest tightened with every step, upon reaching the door.
	join Celestine (half) left
	Celestine: (Okay, Celestine, get it together)
	if {selected_subject} == "english":
		Celestine: What is the right way to ask this? How do I approach him without sounding guilty?
		Celestine: I need to use proper communication strategies to get the information I need.
		[signal arg="start_minigame dialogue_choice_janitor"]
	elif {selected_subject} == "math":
		Celestine: The janitor mentioned he mopped the hallway at 3\:00 PM yesterday.
		Celestine: But wait... I see fresh footprints leading to the faculty room.
		Celestine: The floor dries completely in 45 minutes according to the janitor.
		Celestine: If I can reconstruct the timeline of events mathematically...
		Celestine: I can calculate exactly when someone entered the faculty room!
		[signal arg="start_minigame timeline_footprints_math"]
	elif {selected_subject} == "science":
		Celestine: The janitor said he mopped at 3\:00 PM. The floor dries in 45 minutes in this humidity.
		Celestine: These footprints still have slight moisture. If I apply physics principles...
		Celestine: I can calculate the evaporation rate and determine when they were made!
		[signal arg="start_minigame evaporation_analysis_science"]
	[background arg="res://Bg/storage_room.png" fade="0.0"]
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s2/The_protagonist_enters.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist enters the Storage Room.
	join Celestine (half) left [animation="Slide From Left" length="3.6"]
	join "Janitor Fred" (Janitor_half) right [animation="Slide From Right" length="1.5" move_time="2.0"]
	Celestine: Good afternoon, sir. I was hoping you could help me. I'm looking for something I lost in this room—have you come across anything unusual while you were sweeping?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s2/The_Janitor_brings.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The Janitor brings in his cleaning equipment in the room.
	"Janitor Fred": No young woman, what do you need from me?
	Celestine: I noticed earlier today that there seems to be a problem with the exam papers? Do you know what that's about?
	"Janitor Fred": I overheard them at the faculty earlier panicking about how the exam papers are ruined because they got wet. One air conditioning unit in the faculty room started leaking yesterday. It was noticed by the English teacher this morning.
	Celestine: Huh, those looked pretty new from what I can remember.
	"Janitor Fred": That is why the principal is so mad. He called the store where the air conditioner was bought to complain. The store is sending a repair guy.
	Celestine: Do you know when the repair guy will arrive?
	"Janitor Fred": He'll probably arrive anytime now. I heard the principal say that it will probably be after classes are done for the day.
	Celestine: Thanks for answering my questions.
	"Janitor Fred": No problem kid.
	leave "Janitor Fred" [animation="Slide To Right"]
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s2/Janitor_leaves_the_room.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Janitor leaves the room after checking how dirty it is, but does not clean the room yet.
	Celestine: Hmmm, nothing is really suspicious from what I have gathered so far.
	label choice_1_celestine
	Celestine: What's the most logical next step based on what the Janitor said?
	- The repair guy is the main suspect. | [if {c1s2_repair_tried} == false]
		set {c1s2_repair_tried} = true
		[signal arg="wrong_choice"]
		set {chapter1_score} -= 5
		Celestine: No, that doesn't feel right. The leak was discovered this morning, but happened yesterday. The repair guy was only called today. He's not a suspect.
		jump choice_1_celestine
	- The English teacher is suspicious. | [if {c1s2_teacher_tried} == false]
		set {c1s2_teacher_tried} = true
		[signal arg="wrong_choice"]
		set {chapter1_score} -= 5
		Celestine: The English teacher found the leak, but the Janitor said it started yesterday. I shouldn't jump to conclusions about who found it. The timeline is more important.
		jump choice_1_celestine
	- The timeline of the leak is the key.
		set {chapter1_score} += 10
		Celestine: That's it. The leak happened yesterday, but was only found this morning. What happened in between? That feels like the real mystery.
	Celestine: I have a strange feeling about this. Something doesn't add up. I should keep digging for more information.
	leave --All-- [animation="Slide To Right"]
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s2/The_protagonist_leaves.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist leaves the room and heads for the faculty room.
	jump c1s3/
